definition.value: Conjugate base of isonocardicin A zwitterion where both carboxy groups are deprotonated while the homoserine amino group is protonated.
A morphinane-like compound that is a semi-synthetic opioid synthesized from codeine.
The conjugate acid of benzyl cetraxate; major species at pH 7.3.
Dizwitterionic form of meso-2,6-diaminopimelic acid arising from migration of protons from both carboxy groups to the amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of 1-deoxy-D-xylulose 5-phosphate arising from deprotonation of both phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2'-deoxyribonucleoside triphosphate oxoanion that is a trianion of dGTP, arising from deprotonation of three of the four triphosphate OH groups.
The trianion of a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate.
Conjugate acid of dihydrostreptomycin 6-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the secondary amino and both guanidino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Decaanion of 1D-myo-inositol 1,2,4,5,6-pentakisphosphate arising from global deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A flavonoid oxoanion that is the conjugate base of 4',5,7-trihydroxy-3'-methoxyflavone arising from selective deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of 3-ADP-glyceric acid arising from deprotonation of phosphate and carboxy groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A trivalent inorganic anion obtained by removal of all three protons from cyclotriphosphoric acid.; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate acid of L-tryptophanamide arising from protonation of the alpha-amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of L-serine phosphoethanolamine having anionic phosphate and carboxy groups and both amino groups protonated; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino acid zwitterion of N(2)-acetyl-L-ornithine arising from migration of a proton from the carboxy group to the epsilon-amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Tetraanion of UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine 4,6-bissulfate arising from deprotonation of diphosphate and sulfate groups; major species at pH 7.3.

A nucleotide-sugar oxoanion that is the conjugate base of UDP-2-acetamido-4-amino-2,4,6-trideoxy-D-glucose arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups and protonation of the 4-amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of xanthommatin having both carboxy groups deprotonated and the amino group protonated; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of N-formyl-L-methionine; major species at pH 7.3.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of cortisol phosphate.
Dianion of UDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-D-glucose; major species at pH 7.3.
Trication of sym-homospermidine arising from protonation of all three amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of CMP-N-acetyl-beta-neuraminate arising from deprotonation of carboxylic acid and phosphate functions; major species at pH 7.3.
Trianion of quercetin 3,3',7-trissulfate arising from deprotonation of the three sulfate OH groups.
The conjugate base of triacetic acid; major species at pH 7.3.

A carbohydrate acid derivative anion that is the dianion resulting from the removal of the proton from both of the carboxylic acid groups of luteolin-7-O-[beta-D-glucuronosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucuronide].
A cationic sphingoid obtained by protonation of the amino group of sphinganine.
Trianion of 5,10-methylenetetrahydromethanopterin arising from deprotonation of phosphate and carboxy groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of 3-hydroxyquinolin-4(1H)-one arising from deprotonation of the 3-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of N(6)-hydroxy-L-lysine having an anionic carboxy group and a cationic amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
A dipeptide zwitterion that is the zwitterionic form of D-alanyl-D-alanine arising from migration of a proton from the OH of the carboxy terminus to the amino terminus.
Dianion of 4-CDP-2-C-methyl-D-erythritol arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of oxaluric acid; major species at pH 7.3.
A zwitterionic form of L-lombricine where the carboxy and phosphate groups are anionic and the amino and guanidino groups are cationic; major species at pH 7.3.
Zwitterionic form of 6-aminohexanoic acid arising from migration of a proton from the carboxy group to the amino group; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of D-hamamelose 2(1)-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An organophosphate oxoanion that is the dianion of L-xylulose 5-phosphate arising from deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of cyanidin 3-O-rutinoside 5-O-beta-D-glucoside arising from selective deprotonation of the 7-hydroxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
Conjugate base of glycerol 1,2-cyclic phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
The carboxylate anion of a 1,2-diacyl-3-[3-(alpha-D-N-acetylneuraminyl)-beta-D-galactosyl]-sn-glycerol.
Conjugate base of N-benzoyl-4-hydroxyanthranilic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
An ammonium ion that is the trication of spermidine, formed by protonation at all three nitrogens.
Dication of glutathionylspermidine arising from deprotonation of the terminal carboxy group and protonation of the primary and secondary amino groups; major species at pH 7.3.
The heptaanion of a 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 3,4,5-trisphosphate; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of dTDP-4-dehydro-6-deoxy-D-galactose arising from deprotonation of the diphosphate OH groups; major species at pH 7.3.
Dianion of N-phosphotaurocyamine arising from deprotonation of phosphoramidate and sulfonate OH groups and protonation of the guanidino group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 3-dehydro-2-deoxy-D-gluconic acid; major species at pH 7.3.
